                            <comment id="15152973" author="prasanth_j" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 19:55:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gopalv&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gopalv&quot;&gt;gopalv&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sershe&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sershe&quot;&gt;sershe&lt;/a&gt; Can someone take a look?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153149" author="sershe" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 21:35:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not 100% clear on correct usage of this init code. Will this solve the problems with slf4j automatic &quot;pick random jar&quot; code? Also, why is it not called at the earliest possible point e.g. in main()?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153166" author="prasanth_j" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 21:43:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moved the logging initialization to top. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153179" author="prasanth_j" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 21:47:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not related to SLF4J&apos;s runtime binding. This is just to avoid erroneous autoconfiguration of logging for llap. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gopalv&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gopalv&quot;&gt;gopalv&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s comment &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-13027?focusedCommentId=15150141&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15150141&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-13027?focusedCommentId=15150141&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15150141&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;suspects logging initialized from some other properties files. If for some reason logging is initialized with wrong properties file this initialization (reconfiguration) will make sure llap always uses llap-daemon-log4j2.properties file. Also it prints which file it picked up from classpath.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153186" author="prasanth_j" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 21:50:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LlapDaemon is invoked from other place (MiniLlap) and main(). So added it at top of ctor.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153843" author="gopalv" created="Fri, 19 Feb 2016 07:21:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM - +1, tests pending.&lt;/p&gt;

